    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-04T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="667"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1553: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-04T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 4, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 4—8:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>492. All press this morning report military operations in Abyssinia noting
                    Italian claims of “preventative police action” and no formal declaration of
                    war.</p>
                <p>I have already asked the Foreign Office whether in the view of His Majesty’s
                    Government a state of war exists between Italy and Abyssinia and am awaiting
                    reply.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
